      <title>1836 Mar. 13, Holley Springs, Mississippi [to unknown recipient] / [Adam Fergusson]</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This is a letter dated March 13, 1836. The author is most likely Adam Fergusson. Fergusson writes to discuss the regulations by which the Chickasaw Nation may sell portions of their land. Fergusson also relates a story about a possible corrupt land speculator.</abstract>
